Laeri the Timelost Scholar BOT 21/09/2023 20:41
The tired lad would crack his eyes open from his horrid slumber, awakening in a most unfamiliar place. In a most unfamiliar point in time. His head rose from the floor where he laid, giving a shake of his head as if to shake away the misery of the nightmare he'd just crawled his way through. Grey eyes fluttering their gaze about as he'd slowly begin to clamber up to his feet. Right hand tousling his dark brown locks of hair and letting it hang upon his head in an endearing, if not messy ruffle that framed his feminine features. "Hells below... I feel like death. Can only imagine I look it too." With that, he'd begin to check himself over. Seeming to be intact for the most part. His odd attire simply... not seeming to be relevant in this era whatsoever. Ornately woven dark clothes looking high-class, but from an entirely different generation in spite of his apparent youth. "Right... it appears then that I'm well enough in spite of the headache." he'd murmur to himself. Before looking to the others and smiling with a hint of nervousness. "Would someone be kind enough to explain to me where we are?"
